We ALL have positive AND negative qualities. 

For instance, 

I’m very motivated and driven, AND I have poor administrative skills. 

I’m someone who loves HARD and fiercely protects my friendships, AND I can be too direct if I don’t slow down and choose my words. 

If I can recognize the positive and negative within myself, then it’s okay to recognize the positive and negative within others. 

We’re often so quick to label ourselves and others as “bad” or “good” when in actuality… we all have positive and negative qualities. 

Wisdom holds space for both. It’s only then that you make decisions in light of REALITY, not fantasy.

My freshman year of college, I began searching for a new spirituality. 

After experiencing excruciating heartbreak, I couldn’t fathom serving a God who let me experience it. I got to a point where I denounced my faith in Jesus altogether.

But I tell you what…

“Spiritual” exploration didn’t enlighten me.
“Spiritual” meditation didn’t heal me.
“Spiritual” information didn’t change me.

That… only Jesus did.

So when I came back as a prodigal daughter to her Heavenly Father, I knew better than to leave again. 

After I experienced the spirit of darkness in the world, I could no longer deny the Spirit of Truth.

Jesus opened up my eyes. 
Jesus lifted my burden.
Jesus changed my life.

That’s why I CONFIDENTLY claim Him. 

So if you claim JESUS… say it with ya chest! 

#confidentinchrist #standinconfidence

After Jesus was baptized, the Father affirmed Him by saying, “this is my son, in whom I’m well pleased.”

After Jesus was affirmed, that’s when the Spirit led Him to the wilderness to be tested.

Jesus fasted for 40 days while Satan temped Him 3 separate times. After Jesus passed the test, that’s when He stepped into the fullness of His assignment.

He gained influence, power and authority. He healed the sick, cast out demons and raised the dead. 

So if God has affirmed the call on your life but all you see is opposition, then you’re in good company.

Pass the test. There’s glory on the other side of this. 

#standinconfidence #confidentinchrist

Diagnosis: Spiritual Dysmorphia.

My recommended prescription??

1. Pray for God to help you see yourself accurately. Ask Him to show you how He sees you. And believe it.

2. Read Romans 8 and Ephesians 1 & 2… and MEDITATE on them daily 

3. Heal from the pain of your past and the messages it sent you. It’s clouding your vision. Also seek out deliverance and close any open doors.

4. Start operating as if you are who God says you are. Once you step out in faith with God and you see your power and authority in the spirit, it will grow your spiritual muscles and inevitably deepen your confidence.

We need you on the battlefield, my friend. It’s time to rise up!

You don’t have to have it all figured out in order to have some things figured out. There are people who would LOVE to be blessed by you. Please don’t rob them of that opportunity. 

#calledhigher

cc: Ephesians 1 + 2 🤍
We’re extending the ✨blonde era✨

I HATE the religious spirit!

It’s the one that tells you that you’re no longer legitimate in the sight of God if you’re not affiliated with a person, crowd, camp or denomination. 

There is no BIBLICAL teaching or basis for doctrine of needing a “covering” to be blessed or legitimized. It’s religious jargon. It’s is selling you the lie of SECONDHAND SIGNIFICANCE and it is DEMONIC. 

When it comes to church… Please don’t move from one place of bondage to another because you’re afraid to be “uncovered.” 

You still belong to The Church when you don’t have a church. 

God may (for a set time) be calling you to HIMSELF so He can heal you, deliver you, and restore you. 

Church was God’s idea. And He wants you in the right church even more than you do.

So don’t make it an idol. While there’s a place for honoring spiritual authority, the Lord is your ULTIMATE authority. 

Trust that if you resist the pressure to RUSH into another church to be shepherded only by God, then He will bring you to a place of safety within a church that He hand-picked for you 🤍

BE CONFIDENT IN THAT!!!

Jesus went to immeasurable lengths for you so that YOU could hear Him. Personally. Intimately. Clearly. 

Please stop confessing “I don’t know the voice of God.”

Yes you do!!! If you belong to Him, you are His sheep. And His sheep know His voice.

Maybe you just need to divorce yourself from the LIE that you NEED to go through someone else in order to hear God. You have the SAME ACCESS to God that any other child of God has. 

Others are sent to us as a resource…. to point us back to THE SOURCE 🤍

God loves you so much. And not only does He want to communicate directly with you, but He also made it possible for you to through the Holy Spirit.

If you would like to grow in spiritual confidence so that you have greater assurance that you hear God directly, read these passages:

Hebrews chapters 4-10 
Romans 8
1 Corinthians 3

The full video of this conversation with @avriellemuse is on my YouTube channel, titled “Prophetic Silencing: Being Belittled for Speaking the TRUTH.” 

This conversation is for you if you’ve been sent by God to reveal His truth, but others have attempted to silence you! 

In all of this, my heart is that you find your confidence in CHRIST, and no other place. Because all other foundations are sinking sand. 

#StandinConfidence

About a week ago, @michaeljpittman asked me to show him pictures of flowers that I like because he knows that my taste in flowers has changed since when we first got married almost 9 years ago. 

He said he wanted to be able to adequately surprise me with flowers that I love 🥹

Yesterday, I came home to the most stunning peonies and the sweetest love note.

We’ve been practicing new ways to be even more open and transparent with one another, and it’s so affirming to know that he loves it as much as I do! 

Michael’s not the kind of guy that gets me flowers to make up for a fight. Never happened before. He’s a “just because I love you” kind of giver… which is honestly top notch. 

Man, I love it here 🥰

God is doing a new thing in me.

I have never posted a no-makeup (or lashes), natural hair, no filter, and unedited picture of myself on Instagram. 

And if I’m honest, that’s not good. 

I’ve allowed God to transform so many areas of my life, and use me to do amazing things for Him… all while remaining bound in the area of my appearance. 

And while God has never condemned hair, makeup or filters… I’ve used them as a crutch in many ways.

So I’m now in a season of relying less on these things as a sense of comfort and also returning my praise to God. 

If I’m tempted to praise myself, I’m going to instead praise God. 

If I’m tempted to talk down to myself, I’m going to instead praise God.

I believe that in doing so, God will heal the parts of my soul that I’ve never allowed to heal. 

There’s so much more I could say. But I’ll leave this post here for now as a showcase… 

it may be a sign for some of you, but for me, it’s an act of obedience and laying myself low. It’s me fighting for my freedom!

#confidentinchrist

For most of my life, the enemy’s attack against me was to make me believe that I am unworthy of love.

And all the while, the name my parents gave me has been a prophetic declaration of God’s love for me. Victory over unworthiness is in my name! 

And to think that this is all possible because I’ve found refuge in the name above all names 🙌🏼

God never stops revealing pieces of my soul that have been trapped in captivity to show me the path to freedom. 

So even though this is a vulnerable process for me, hair + makeup are far too trivial to keep “off limits” from God. 

I will do my part so that God gets the glory out of EVERY area of my life. 

God is in the business of redeeming the things that the enemy has perverted so that we can experience them in the way that He intended.

So I praise Him in advance for the freedom, glory, and beauty on the other side! 

#confidenceinchrist

One of my fave quotes goes, “when God created purpose for your life, your stupidity was factored in.”

So you do your part and let God do His! 

#standinconfidence #confidentinchrist

Something I’ve been working hard on this past month… is prepping for HOMESCHOOL!

My son Elijah is starting 2nd grade homeschool in just ONE WEEK!!!! 

I’m so excited!! 

At first I was very intimidated by the thought of doing this. 

…How would I also get work done? 

…Where do I start?! 

But once I pushed past the fears and started researching curriculum, testing Elijah’s grade placement, mapping out our weekly flow, and working on our homeschool room… my inner teacher came out 😂

(I used to be an elementary school music teacher 😜🎶)

We’re looking at Michael teaching him 2x a week and me teaching 2x a week, and eventually bringing in a teacher to help us support the load! 

All of this is subject to change after we get into the swing of things and feel it out, but I’m SO EXCITED to see how this all flows! Next year, we’ll have Lily learn at home too. 

Cheers to:
- no unwanted indoctrination
- more time with our kids
- keeping Christ at the center
- more lifestyle flexibility 
- trying something new 

🥰

I have the BIGGEST crush on this guy 🤭😍

We’ve been together for 10 years, married for 9, and I’m still obsessed with @mr.mjpittman. 

Here are 5 marriage nuggets that have kept us HAPPILY married:

1. Honor one another. Don’t belittle, be hyper critical of, or embarrass your spouse. Be their BIGGEST fan!

2. Be one another’s escape. Escapism AWAY from marriage is a huge temptation for people who’ve grown bored. But when you can’t WAIT to talk about anything and everything with your spouse and try new fun things with them… they become your escape from the weight of life.

3. Everyone else gets the polished, buttoned-up version of you. But when only your partner gets the 100% unfiltered version of you, you become one another’s safe place. When you slowly build trust and space for vulnerability, being your “undone” self and seeing their “unhinged” feels incredible. I can’t get enough 🙌🏼

4. We’ve been waking up at 5:30a each morning to pray together and talk through our daily priorities. This has been some of the sweetest times where we go down rabbit trails and make relational deposits before the day (or our kids) gets the best of us. 

5. Study your spouse!! When you’re genuinely interested in one another and you don’t assume you know everything there is to know, things get fun 🙌🏼 I’m not married to the same man from 9 years ago, nor is he married to the same woman. Keep learning each other! 

Sn… he just keeps getting finer 🤤 so that helps too 😂

Anyone else still head over heels?!

One of the greatest catalysts for your calling… is who you say “I do” to. 

This picture of @mr.mjpittman and I was taken about a year ago at my book launch party for Stand in Confidence. 

Let me tell you… there is absolutely no way that I would have been able to host a conference and release two books last year without this man. 

His belief in me, his support with the kids, and his willingness to invest in what God called me to do is what made it all possible.

Likewise, I’m his biggest cheerleader. I hold it down at home while he’s on meetings with clients, taking business trips, and doing speaking engagements. I’m brainstorming with him on business. 

He lets me content create, explore my creative ideas, and even spend time with friends that inspire me.

I let him focus on his gains in the gym, talk for hours on the phone with his business-minded buddies, and take opportunities he shouldn’t miss.

What’s the point in all this?

Your spouse can either be wind in your sails, or a parachute on your back. They will either propel you forward or hold you back.

So when it comes to marriage, CHOOSE WISELY. 

And if you’re already married… may your presence in their life be the reason why they become all that God created them to be.

God cares about FAMILY. 

If you look with spiritual eyes, it’s plain as day that there’s a cultural attack on marriage and family. 

God designed husband and wife to be one with one another and one Him. That unity is the foundation of society.

That’s why I have LOVED visiting @focusonthefamily with @mr.mjpittman and learning the ways that they’re praying and planning to reach the next generation. It is NECESSARY!

there way no question that God’s seemingly-“extra” instructions are truly our battle-winning strategies.

Parenthood isn’t easy, and starting a family young isn’t for everyone. 

That said, I LOVE being a dad to my babies and I have experienced even more “life” since they’ve arrived! 

I am seeing a POSITIVE trend of men being more committed as involved, present, and loving fathers. My timeline is full of them!

🫡 SALUTE to all the great dads out there!

Motherhood lately 🤍

They keep my life colorful.

“There’s a blessing with my name on it!”

YES. 

…aaaaand….

We can’t sit around and wait for things to fall in our laps. Faith without works is DEAD! 

You gotta be willing to do the work that it takes to access the blessings God has in store for you.

These past four days in the Dominican Republic have been incredible. 

My husband and I flew down to visit the local churches and communities that @compassion serve, love, and resource. And man… seeing the work firsthand… 

It’s SPECIAL. 
It’s NEEDED. 
It’s REAL.

The DR is particularly special to me because my dad grew up in extreme poverty just like these children. 

He immigrated to America from the DR after high school because a wealthy couple had compassion on him, took him under their wing, financed him to move to Texas, and shared the gospel with him.

My dad gave up alcoholism, fighting, and his old way of life to follow Jesus. He met my mom and gave us a better life than he ever imagined. And it was all made possible because someone cared enough to take ACTION. 

Not only have my parents been missionaries in the DR, but @mr.mjpittman and I have sponsored several children because the need is bigger than you could fathom.

So meeting the children at these churches that Compassion partners with only deepened my conviction to take a stand against the giant of poverty and care for whom God considers the greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven.

I want to invite you into the opportunity to be the hands and feet of Jesus by taking action. 

You don’t have to be wealthy to make a difference!!

When you sponsor a child for $43 a month, it provides them with food, regular medical checkups, educational support, and a tangible introduction to the love of God.

Plus, it means the world to the kiddos when you write them letters and let them know that they matter. 

Go click the Compassion lynk in my profile to sponsor a child and change their life! 

Change starts one person at a time!
